The article discusses President Trump's remarks on the establishment of the United States Space Command. The President announced that Vice President Mike Pence will be sent to Poland in his place due to an approaching storm. The President emphasized that the safety and security of the people in the path of the hurricane is the highest priority. He then discussed the importance of the United States Space Command in defending America's interests in space, highlighting the weaponization of Earth's orbits by adversaries and the need to protect American satellites. The President also praised General Jay Raymond, the new leader of SPACECOM, and expressed his support for the establishment of the United States Space Force as the sixth branch of the Armed Forces. The President concluded by acknowledging the advancements made in the military budget and the importance of preparing for victory to prevent conflict. The article includes the signing of documents to formally establish the United States Space Command and the unfurling of the flag of the command.